INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew04: Babies start to sleep from 4 weeks after conception
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew05: From conception to birth, a baby's weight increases 3,000 million times
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew06: Your baby has an identifiable heartbeat just six weeks into your pregnancy
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew07: Thumb sucking has been detected in babies from as early as 7 weeks
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew08: Your baby's little fingers and toes are starting to change from being titchy buds into actual digits
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew09: Babies begin kicking soon after nine weeks but you won't feel it until week 16-22
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew10: Your baby will start to use one hand more than the other, the same one they'll prefer to use after birth
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew11: Your feet can grow one full size during pregnancy
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew12: Your baby's little wrists and elbows bend now as they move around
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew13: Baby's finger nails and toe nails are forming
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew14: Dribbling on your pillow at night? Excess saliva is common during pregnancy
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew15: Your baby will have started to grow a layer of fine downy hair called lanugo
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew16: Your baby's eyes are becoming sensitive to light and they will turn away if a bright light is shone on mum's belly
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew17: Your baby can make a fist and suck its thumb now
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew18: About 30% of pregnant women snore because of increased swelling in their nasal passages
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew19: In the womb babies develop a waxy, cream cheese-like coating called vernix. Some are born with vernix residue
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew20: By now your baby can hear your heartbeat and outside noises like music
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew21: Pregnancy is the only time in life when you'll fall in love with someone you haven't met
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew22: It's sometimes suggested (but not proven) baby's heart rate is under 140 beats minute if it's a boy, and if faster it's a girl
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew23: The average size of a full-term baby in the UK is 7.7lbs
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew24: Your baby's face will now be fully formed with eyelashes, eyebrows and hair
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew25: Baby's little lungs are now maturing so they can breathe actual air rather than fluid
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew26: Around about now your baby will be opening his/her eyes for the first time
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew27: Mums who exclusively breastfeed can burn as many as 600 calories a day.
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew28: Feel out of breath? It's due to the pressure from the growing uterus as the diaphragm cannot be drawn down as far during inhalation
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew29: Your baby will double in size between now and birth!
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew31: Your baby's eyes can now tell when it is light or dark
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew30: Many women report an increase in vivid dreams especially during the final trimester
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew32: Eating the placenta goes back as far as the 1500s in Chinese medicine - but the jury's still out on its benefits!
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew33: When babies are born, parts of their skull may overlap to help them squeeze out - leaving the head temporarily cone-shaped after delivery
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew34: The placenta can weigh around 2lbs and the combined length of the blood vessels in your placenta is 32 miles!
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew35: 1 in 3 women have an epidural and 9 out of 10 find it effective
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew36: A sweep is a vaginal examination and involves placing a finger inside the cervix and making circular, sweeping movement as a 'soft' way of inducing labour
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew37: Your baby is gaining about half a pound a week
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew38: Orgasms can induce contractions because sperm contains prostaglandin and can stimulate the uterus
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew39: Only five per cent of babies are born on their due date (so don't count on it!)
INTRO_TAGLINE.Prew40: Most women choose an epidural when they're around 5cm dilated - 8-9cm is often too late
